  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">United Nations Humanitarian Air Service (UNHAS) Afghanistan: Domestic services and international airbridge for humanitarian community</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With this support, UNHAS transports an average of around 1,500 passengers per month to and from 22 domestic locations in Afghanistan and one international route to and from Islamabad, Pakistan through the international airbridge.  UNHAS enables the humanitarian community to implement their humanitarian assistance and user organizations to access hard to reach destinations where travelling by roads is a big security risk in Afghanistan. All humanitarian organizations, which heavily rely on UNHAS, are engaged in various emergencies while undertaking relief and recovery activities, development projects, and other humanitarian responses embracing refugees, IDPs, agriculture, education, child care, gender and women empowerment, human rights, capacity building, health, nutrition, emergency food distribution and food need assessment in various provinces in the country to name but a few.  As a demand-driven, user and impact oriented common service, UNHAS has a capacity of rapid adaptation to meet the air transport needs of the humanitarian community in emergency situations, including medical and security relocation.</narrative>
  </description>
